V<<sidebar "Career resources while abroad">>\u000aThe Center for Student Professional Development (CSPD) has many career resources available to you while you are abroad. Start with the [[Information for Students Studying Abroad|http://www.vanderbilt.edu/career/students/studyabroad.php]] page to become acquainted with resources and frequently asked questions from students.\u000a\u000a''Need a coaching appointment while abroad? No problem!''\u000a\u000aAll of CSPD\u2019s career coaches are available by phone, Skype, and email throughout the year to answer your questions and to help you explore and pursue jobs and internships. \u000a\u000a|box|k\u000a|!To schedule an appointment call or email the Center|\u000a|Phone: 615-322-2750|\u000a|Email: [[careercenter@vanderbilt.edu|mailto:careercenter@vanderbilt.edu]]|\u000a|Website:[[www.vanderbilt.edu/career|http://www.vanderbilt.edu/career]]|\u000a\u000a''What do I do if I am invited to interview while I am abroad?''\u000a\u000aReach out and let the company know that you are abroad. Ask if they would be able to set up a Skype or phone interview with you instead. If you found the job through DoreWays and you cannot find the contact information for the company, email [[recruiting@vanderbilt.edu|mailto:recruiting@vanderbilt.edu]] for assistance. //Remember the time difference of your country when contacting them and scheduling interviews.//\u000a\u000a''Please contact the CSPD office with any questions. They are here to support you!''\u000a\u000a<<segue "Conduct and law">>\u005c
